33 informing the person of the trust's existence, of the trustee's name and address,
34 and of the time allowed for commencing a proceeding.
35 (b) Upon the death of the settlor of a trust that was revocable at the settlor's death, the
36 trustee may proceed to administer the trust and distribute the trust property in accordance with
37 the terms of the trust. The trustee is trust and shall not be subject to liability for doing so unless:so,
38 except that the trustee shall not distribute trust property to any beneficiary in contravention of the
