General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (f) If no administrator has been appointed, the clerk of superior court shall, upon motion
2 of the clerk or upon the application of an interested party, disburse the money received under this
3 section for the following purposes and in the following order:
4 (1) To pay the surviving spouse's year's allowance and children's year's allowance
5 assigned in accordance with law.law, except that if (i) it has been greater than
6 six months since the date of death of the decedent and (ii) there has been no
7 petition filed and assignment of a spouse's or child's year's allowance, the clerk
8 may disburse the money received under this section in accordance with the
9 other provisions of this subsection.
10 (2), (3) Repealed by Session Laws 1981, c. 383, s. 3.
11 (4) All other claims shall be disbursed according to the order set out in
12 G.S. 28A-19-6.
13 Notwithstanding the foregoing provisions of this subsection, the clerk shall pay, out of funds
14 provided the deceased pursuant to G.S. 111-18 and Part 3 of Article 2 of Chapter 108A of the
15 General Statutes of North Carolina, Statutes, any lawful claims for care provided by an adult care
16 home to the deceased, incurred not more than 90 days prior to the deceased's death. After the
17 death of a spouse who died intestate the decedent and after the disbursements have been made in
18 accordance with this subsection, the balance in the clerk's hands belonging to the estate of the
19 decedent shall be paid to the surviving spouse, and if there is no surviving spouse, the clerk shall
20 pay it to the heirs or beneficiaries in proportion to their respective interests.
21 (g) The clerk shall not be required to publish notice to creditors.
22 (h) Whenever an administrator is appointed after a clerk of superior court has received
23 any money pursuant to this section, the clerk shall pay to the administrator all funds which have
24 not been disbursed. The clerk shall receive no commissions for payments made to the
25 administrator, and the administrator shall receive no commissions for receiving such payments."
26 SECTION 4.6. This Part becomes effective January 1, 2026, and applies to petitions
27 filed on or after that date.
28
29 PART V. EFFECTIVE DATE
30 SECTION 5.1. Except as otherwise provided in this act, this act is effective when it
31 becomes law.
